Model Charter
Credit Spread Regime Model Charter
Model Name: Credit Spread Regime Model
Short Name: CSRM
Version: v1.0
Status: Research / Development
Model Type: Deterministic macro regime classification model
Primary Domain: Credit, macro stress, cross-asset confirmation
Implementation Style: Functional Python module
Primary Role: Macro overlay / regime engine / risk filter
________________________________________
1. Objective
The Credit Spread Regime Model is designed to classify the daily macro credit environment into interpretable risk regimes using credit-sensitive ETF proxies and supporting cross-asset signals.
The model converts credit behavior into:
•	a continuous composite regime score
•	a discrete regime label
•	diagnostic sub-scores
•	transition / warning flags
•	a latest-state interpretation snapshot
The model is intended to support:
•	macro regime detection
•	equity risk filtering
•	defensive rotation logic
•	allocation overlays
•	cross-asset confirmation
•	trading risk posture adjustments
________________________________________
2. Core Financial Logic
Credit spreads reflect the market’s pricing of default risk, liquidity stress, and general risk appetite.
When credit conditions improve, risky credit typically outperforms safe Treasuries and lower-quality credit often outperforms higher-quality credit. That tends to align with a healthier macro environment and stronger willingness to take risk.
When credit conditions deteriorate, high yield and investment grade credit tend to weaken relative to Treasuries, internal credit breadth worsens, and divergence versus equities can appear before equity markets fully reprice.
The model approximates this logic using:
•	HYG, JNK, LQD
•	SHY, IEF, TLT
•	SPY
•	VIX
________________________________________
3. Model Scope
The v1 model will:
1.	ingest daily aligned market data
2.	construct credit proxy ratios
3.	engineer trend, stress, breadth, divergence, and persistence features
4.	normalize features with rolling transformations
5.	compute interpretable sub-scores
6.	compute a final composite regime score
7.	assign a discrete regime label
8.	emit diagnostic flags and latest snapshot explanation
The model will not in v1:
•	fit ML models
•	optimize weights by backtest
•	forecast returns directly
•	run a full portfolio backtest
•	use proprietary spread analytics by default
